- MT2      : Elastic angular distribution                         1025 1451
                                                                  1025 1451
The flag LTT=3 is used to indicate a switch at some high energy,  1025 1451
generally 50 MeV, from a Legendre representation to a tabulated   1025 1451
representation. For incident energies below this energy, the      1025 1451
Legendre coefficients are given on a sufficiently precise energy  1025 1451
grid. They are a sum of calculated Legendre coefficients for      1025 1451
compound nucleus and shape-elastic scattering. For higher         1025 1451
incident energies, relative angular distributions are tabulated   1025 1451
